items.title: SBI Q1 Results Preview: Mixed PAT growth likely; muted NII seen amid margin pressure. Check these 6 metrics
items.description: SBI’s Q1 FY26 results are expected to show moderate bottom-line growth amid contracting NIMs, higher provisions, and tepid loan growth. Analysts flag margin trends, credit costs, and asset quality as key metrics to track. PAT is estimated between Rs 16,530–19,576 crore.

items.title: Transrail Q1 Results: Net profit more than doubles to Rs 106 cr; order book crosses Rs 14K cr level
items.description: Transrail Lighting has said its net profit more than doubled to Rs 106 crore in the June quarter of FY26, pushed by higher revenues from core business segments.

items.title: India's Bajaj Electricals Q1 Results: Profit plunges 97% YoY on weak demand, one-time charge
items.description: India's Bajaj Electricals reported a 96.8% slump in first-quarter profit on Thursday, hurt by lower demand for its home appliances and a one-off expense.

items.title: Tata Motors Q1 Preview: PAT likely to drop 36% YoY, hurt by JLR and domestic headwinds
items.description: Tata Motors is expected to report weak Q1FY26 results, with a sharp YoY drop in PAT and revenue due to sluggish volumes across JLR and domestic segments. Analysts foresee margin pressures from operating leverage, input costs, and forex challenges, while commentary on demand trends and margins will be closely tracked.
